{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T00:30:57.664Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt templates and variables"},{"type":"text","text":" transform prompt engineering from scattered text into "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"maintainable, versioned configuration"},{"type":"text","text":". Instead of hard-coding prompts across your codebase, templates treat prompts as first-class assets that are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"versioned, validated, and dynamically rendered"},{"type":"text","text":" with runtime values."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The key concept:"},{"type":"text","text":" A template separates "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prompt logic from application code"},{"type":"text","text":", enabling safe variable injection and reusable components."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Prompt Templates Are"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core Definition"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Prompt templates allow you to create reusable prompts with dynamic placeholders that get filled in at runtime. Instead of hardcoding values, you define placeholders (variables) that can be swapped with actual data when the prompt is used.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template structure:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Role: You are a senior Python engineer\nTask: Write a function to calculate {function_name}\nContext: For a {project_type} project\nFormat: Return code with type hints and docstring"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Variables use:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{{variable_name}}"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{variable_name}"},{"type":"text","text":" syntax"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Use Templates & Variables"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Separates Logic from Code"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"A good template system separates prompt logic from application code, enables safe variable injection, supports composition of complex prompts from reusable components, and provides tooling for testing and iteration.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompts in one place"},{"type":"text","text":" — Not scattered across code\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Safe variable injection"},{"type":"text","text":" — Prevents injection errors\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reusable components"},{"type":"text","text":" — Compose from templates\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Testing tooling"},{"type":"text","text":" — Built-in validation"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Version Control"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Prompt template management solves this by treating prompts as first-class configuration—versioned, validated, and dynamically rendered.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Versioning capabilities:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Create versions"},{"type":"text","text":" — Save prompt iterations\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Compare versions"},{"type":"text","text":" — A/B test variants\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Roll back"},{"type":"text","text":" — Revert to previous\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Track history"},{"type":"text","text":" — See changes over time"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Dynamic Flexibility"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"You can include variables in the prompt so that you can adjust the prompt for different use cases.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flexibility:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Runtime substitution"},{"type":"text","text":" — Fill values at execution\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Different use cases"},{"type":"text","text":" — Same template, different data\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Model flexibility"},{"type":"text","text":" — Adjust for different models"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Template Syntax & Variable Formats"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Variable Syntax Options"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Format"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Syntax"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":nul